5479  int i;

5484  s->malloc_size = rt->malloc_state.malloc_size;
5485  s->malloc_limit = rt->malloc_state.malloc_limit;

5487  s->memory_used_count = 2; /* rt + rt->class_array */
5488  s->memory_used_size = sizeof(JSRuntime) + sizeof(JSValue) * rt->class_count;
5489 
5490  list_for_each(el, &rt->context_list) {
5491  JSContext *ctx = list_entry(el, JSContext, link);
5492  JSShape *sh = ctx->array_shape;
5493  s->memory_used_count += 2; /* ctx + ctx->class_proto */
5494  s->memory_used_size += sizeof(JSContext) +
5495  sizeof(JSValue) * rt->class_count;
5496  s->binary_object_count += ctx->binary_object_count;
5497  s->binary_object_size += ctx->binary_object_size;
5498 
5499  /* the hashed shapes are counted separately */
5500  if (sh && !sh->is_hashed) {
5501  int hash_size = sh->prop_hash_mask + 1;
5502  s->shape_count++;
5503  s->shape_size += get_shape_size(hash_size, sh->prop_size);
5504  }
5505  list_for_each(el1, &ctx->loaded_modules) {
5506  JSModuleDef *m = list_entry(el1, JSModuleDef, link);
5507  s->memory_used_count += 1;
5508  s->memory_used_size += sizeof(*m);
5509  if (m->req_module_entries) {
5510  s->memory_used_count += 1;
5511  s->memory_used_size += m->req_module_entries_count * sizeof(*m->req_module_entries);
5512  }
5513  if (m->export_entries) {
5514  s->memory_used_count += 1;
5515  s->memory_used_size += m->export_entries_count * sizeof(*m->export_entries);
5516  for (i = 0; i < m->export_entries_count; i++) {
5517  JSExportEntry *me = &m->export_entries[i];
5518  if (me->export_type == JS_EXPORT_TYPE_LOCAL && me->u.local.var_ref) {
5519  /* potential multiple count */
5520  s->memory_used_count += 1;
5521  compute_value_size(me->u.local.var_ref->value, hp);
5522  }
5523  }
5524  }
5525  if (m->star_export_entries) {
5526  s->memory_used_count += 1;
5527  s->memory_used_size += m->star_export_entries_count * sizeof(*m->star_export_entries);
5528  }
5529  if (m->import_entries) {
5530  s->memory_used_count += 1;
5531  s->memory_used_size += m->import_entries_count * sizeof(*m->import_entries);
5532  }
5533  compute_value_size(m->module_ns, hp);
5534  compute_value_size(m->func_obj, hp);
5535  }
5536  }
5537 
5538  list_for_each(el, &rt->obj_list) {
5539  JSObject *p = list_entry(el, JSObject, link);
5540  JSShape *sh = p->shape;
5541  JSShapeProperty *prs;
5542  s->obj_count++;
5543  if (p->prop) {
5544  s->memory_used_count++;
5545  s->prop_size += sh->prop_size * sizeof(*p->prop);
5546  s->prop_count += sh->prop_count;
5547  prs = get_shape_prop(sh);
5548  for(i = 0; i < sh->prop_count; i++) {
5549  JSProperty *pr = &p->prop[i];
5550  if (prs->atom != JS_ATOM_NULL && !(prs->flags & JS_PROP_TMASK)) {
5551  compute_value_size(pr->u.value, hp);
5552  }
5553  prs++;
5554  }
5555  }
5556  /* the hashed shapes are counted separately */
5557  if (!sh->is_hashed) {
5558  int hash_size = sh->prop_hash_mask + 1;
5559  s->shape_count++;
5560  s->shape_size += get_shape_size(hash_size, sh->prop_size);
5561  }
5562 
5563  switch(p->class_id) {
5564  case JS_CLASS_ARRAY: /* u.array | length */
5565  case JS_CLASS_ARGUMENTS: /* u.array | length */
5566  s->array_count++;
5567  if (p->fast_array) {
5568  s->fast_array_count++;
5569  if (p->u.array.u.values) {
5570  s->memory_used_count++;
5571  s->memory_used_size += p->u.array.count *
5572  sizeof(*p->u.array.u.values);
5573  s->fast_array_elements += p->u.array.count;
5574  for (i = 0; i < p->u.array.count; i++) {
5575  compute_value_size(p->u.array.u.values[i], hp);
5576  }
5577  }
5578  }
5579  break;
5580  case JS_CLASS_NUMBER: /* u.object_data */
5581  case JS_CLASS_STRING: /* u.object_data */
5582  case JS_CLASS_BOOLEAN: /* u.object_data */
5583  case JS_CLASS_SYMBOL: /* u.object_data */
5584  case JS_CLASS_DATE: /* u.object_data */
5585 #ifdef CONFIG_BIGNUM
5586  case JS_CLASS_BIG_INT: /* u.object_data */
5587  case JS_CLASS_BIG_FLOAT: /* u.object_data */
5588 #endif
5589  compute_value_size(p->u.object_data, hp);
5590  break;
5591  case JS_CLASS_C_FUNCTION: /* u.cfunc */
5592  s->c_func_count++;
5593  break;
5594  case JS_CLASS_BYTECODE_FUNCTION: /* u.func */
5595  {
5596  JSFunctionBytecode *b = p->u.func.function_bytecode;
5597  JSVarRef **var_refs = p->u.func.var_refs;
5598  /* home_object: object will be accounted for in list scan */
5599  if (var_refs) {
5600  s->memory_used_count++;
5601  s->js_func_size += b->closure_var_count * sizeof(*var_refs);
5602  for (i = 0; i < b->closure_var_count; i++) {
5603  if (var_refs[i]) {
5604  double ref_count = var_refs[i]->header.ref_count;
5605  s->memory_used_count += 1 / ref_count;
5606  s->js_func_size += sizeof(*var_refs[i]) / ref_count;
5607  /* handle non object closed values */
5608  if (var_refs[i]->pvalue == &var_refs[i]->value) {
5609  /* potential multiple count */
5610  compute_value_size(var_refs[i]->value, hp);
5611  }
5612  }
5613  }
5614  }
5615  compute_bytecode_size(b, hp);
5616  }
5617  break;
5618  case JS_CLASS_BOUND_FUNCTION: /* u.bound_function */
5619  {
5620  JSBoundFunction *bf = p->u.bound_function;
5621  /* func_obj and this_val are objects */
5622  for (i = 0; i < bf->argc; i++) {
5623  compute_value_size(bf->argv[i], hp);
5624  }
5625  s->memory_used_count += 1;
5626  s->memory_used_size += sizeof(*bf) + bf->argc * sizeof(*bf->argv);
5627  }
5628  break;
5629  case JS_CLASS_C_FUNCTION_DATA: /* u.c_function_data_record */
5630  {
5631  JSCFunctionDataRecord *fd = p->u.c_function_data_record;
5632  if (fd) {
5633  for (i = 0; i < fd->data_len; i++) {
5634  compute_value_size(fd->data[i], hp);
5635  }
5636  s->memory_used_count += 1;
5637  s->memory_used_size += sizeof(*fd) + fd->data_len * sizeof(*fd->data);
5638  }
5639  }
5640  break;
5641  case JS_CLASS_REGEXP: /* u.regexp */
5642  compute_jsstring_size(p->u.regexp.pattern, hp);
5643  compute_jsstring_size(p->u.regexp.bytecode, hp);
5644  break;
5645 
5646  case JS_CLASS_FOR_IN_ITERATOR: /* u.for_in_iterator */
5647  {
5648  JSForInIterator *it = p->u.for_in_iterator;
5649  if (it) {
5650  compute_value_size(it->obj, hp);
5651  s->memory_used_count += 1;
5652  s->memory_used_size += sizeof(*it);
5653  }
5654  }
5655  break;
5656  case JS_CLASS_ARRAY_BUFFER: /* u.array_buffer */
5657  case JS_CLASS_SHARED_ARRAY_BUFFER: /* u.array_buffer */
5658  {
5659  JSArrayBuffer *abuf = p->u.array_buffer;
5660  if (abuf) {
5661  s->memory_used_count += 1;
5662  s->memory_used_size += sizeof(*abuf);
5663  if (abuf->data) {
5664  s->memory_used_count += 1;
5665  s->memory_used_size += abuf->byte_length;
5666  }
5667  }
5668  }
5669  break;
5670  case JS_CLASS_GENERATOR: /* u.generator_data */
5671  case JS_CLASS_UINT8C_ARRAY: /* u.typed_array / u.array */
5672  case JS_CLASS_INT8_ARRAY: /* u.typed_array / u.array */
5673  case JS_CLASS_UINT8_ARRAY: /* u.typed_array / u.array */
5674  case JS_CLASS_INT16_ARRAY: /* u.typed_array / u.array */
5675  case JS_CLASS_UINT16_ARRAY: /* u.typed_array / u.array */
5676  case JS_CLASS_INT32_ARRAY: /* u.typed_array / u.array */
5677  case JS_CLASS_UINT32_ARRAY: /* u.typed_array / u.array */
5678 #ifdef CONFIG_BIGNUM
5679  case JS_CLASS_BIG_INT64_ARRAY: /* u.typed_array / u.array */
5680  case JS_CLASS_BIG_UINT64_ARRAY: /* u.typed_array / u.array */
5681 #endif
5682  case JS_CLASS_FLOAT32_ARRAY: /* u.typed_array / u.array */
5683  case JS_CLASS_FLOAT64_ARRAY: /* u.typed_array / u.array */
5684  case JS_CLASS_DATAVIEW: /* u.typed_array */
5685 #ifdef CONFIG_BIGNUM
5686  case JS_CLASS_FLOAT_ENV: /* u.float_env */
5687 #endif
5688  case JS_CLASS_MAP: /* u.map_state */
5689  case JS_CLASS_SET: /* u.map_state */
5690  case JS_CLASS_WEAKMAP: /* u.map_state */
5691  case JS_CLASS_WEAKSET: /* u.map_state */
5692  case JS_CLASS_MAP_ITERATOR: /* u.map_iterator_data */
5693  case JS_CLASS_SET_ITERATOR: /* u.map_iterator_data */
5694  case JS_CLASS_ARRAY_ITERATOR: /* u.array_iterator_data */
5695  case JS_CLASS_STRING_ITERATOR: /* u.array_iterator_data */
5696  case JS_CLASS_PROXY: /* u.proxy_data */
5697  case JS_CLASS_PROMISE: /* u.promise_data */
5698  case JS_CLASS_PROMISE_RESOLVE_FUNCTION: /* u.promise_function_data */
5699  case JS_CLASS_PROMISE_REJECT_FUNCTION: /* u.promise_function_data */
5700  case JS_CLASS_ASYNC_FUNCTION_RESOLVE: /* u.async_function_data */
5701  case JS_CLASS_ASYNC_FUNCTION_REJECT: /* u.async_function_data */
5702  case JS_CLASS_ASYNC_FROM_SYNC_ITERATOR: /* u.async_from_sync_iterator_data */
5703  case JS_CLASS_ASYNC_GENERATOR: /* u.async_generator_data */
5704  /* TODO */
5705  default:
5706  /* XXX: class definition should have an opaque block size */
5707  if (p->u.opaque) {
5708  s->memory_used_count += 1;
5709  }
5710  break;
5711  }
5712  }
5713  s->obj_size += s->obj_count * sizeof(JSObject);
5714 
5715  /* hashed shapes */
5716  s->memory_used_count++; /* rt->shape_hash */
5717  s->memory_used_size += sizeof(rt->shape_hash[0]) * rt->shape_hash_size;
5718  for(i = 0; i < rt->shape_hash_size; i++) {
5719  JSShape *sh;
5720  for(sh = rt->shape_hash[i]; sh != NULL; sh = sh->shape_hash_next) {
5721  int hash_size = sh->prop_hash_mask + 1;
5722  s->shape_count++;
5723  s->shape_size += get_shape_size(hash_size, sh->prop_size);
5724  }
5725  }
5726 
5727  /* atoms */
5728  s->memory_used_count += 2; /* rt->atom_array, rt->atom_hash */
5729  s->atom_count = rt->atom_count;
5730  s->atom_size = sizeof(rt->atom_array[0]) * rt->atom_size +
5731  sizeof(rt->atom_hash[0]) * rt->atom_hash_size;
5732  for(i = 0; i < rt->atom_size; i++) {
5733  JSAtomStruct *p = rt->atom_array[i];
5734  if (!atom_is_free(p)) {
5735  s->atom_size += (sizeof(*p) + (p->len << p->is_wide_char) +
5736  1 - p->is_wide_char);
5737  }
5738  }
5739  s->str_count = round(mem.str_count);
5740  s->str_size = round(mem.str_size);
5741  s->js_func_count = round(mem.js_func_count);
5742  s->js_func_size = round(mem.js_func_size);
5743  s->js_func_code_size = round(mem.js_func_code_size);
5744  s->js_func_pc2line_count = round(mem.js_func_pc2line_count);
5745  s->js_func_pc2line_size = round(mem.js_func_pc2line_size);
5746  s->memory_used_count += round(mem.memory_used_count) +
5747  s->atom_count + s->str_count +
5748  s->obj_count + s->shape_count +
5749  s->js_func_count + s->js_func_pc2line_count;
5750  s->memory_used_size += s->atom_size + s->str_size +
5751  s->obj_size + s->prop_size + s->shape_size +
5752  s->js_func_size + s->js_func_code_size + s->js_func_pc2line_size;
5753 }

3537  while (p < p_end) {
3538  if (*p < 128) {
3539  string_buffer_putc8(b, *p++);
3540  } else {
3541  /* parse utf-8 sequence, return 0xFFFFFFFF for error */
3542  c = unicode_from_utf8(p, p_end - p, &p_next);
3543  if (c < 0x10000) {
3544  p = p_next;
3545  } else if (c <= 0x10FFFF) {
3546  p = p_next;
3547  /* surrogate pair */
3548  c -= 0x10000;
3549  string_buffer_putc16(b, (c >> 10) + 0xd800);
3550  c = (c & 0x3ff) + 0xdc00;
3551  } else {
3552  /* invalid char */
3553  c = 0xfffd;
3554  /* skip the invalid chars */
3555  /* XXX: seems incorrect. Why not just use c = *p++; ? */
3556  while (p < p_end && (*p >= 0x80 && *p < 0xc0))
3557  p++;
3558  if (p < p_end) {
3559  p++;
3560  while (p < p_end && (*p >= 0x80 && *p < 0xc0))
3561  p++;
3562  }
3563  }
3564  string_buffer_putc16(b, c);
3565  }
3566  }
3567  }
3568  return string_buffer_end(b);
3569 
3570  fail:
3571  string_buffer_free(b);
3572  return JS_EXCEPTION;
3573 }
